description:
http://www.learningconstruction.com  Step by Step Tutorials:  

Learn what is a french drain or a perimeter drain with this quick video.


A French drain[1] or weeping tile (also blind drain,[1] rubble drain,[1] rock drain,[1] drain tile, perimeter drain, land drain or French ditch) is a trench covered with gravel or rock or containing a perforated pipe that redirects surface and groundwater away from an area. A French drain can have perforated hollow pipes along the bottom (see images) to quickly vent water that seeps down through the upper gravel or rock. French drains are common drainage systems, primarily used to prevent ground and surface water from penetrating or damaging building foundations. Alternatively, the French drain technique may be used to distribute water, such as a septic drain field at the outlet of a typical septic tank sewage treatment system. French drains are also used behind retaining walls to relieve ground water pressure.

Foundation
French drains are often installed around a home foundation in two different ways:
Buried around the foundation wall on the external side of the foundation
Installed underneath the basement floor on the inside perimeter of the basement
In most homes, an external French drain or drain tile is installed around the foundation walls before the foundation soil is backfilled. It's laid on the bottom of the excavated area, and a layer of stone is laid on top. In many cases, a filter fabric is then laid on top of the stone to keep fine sediments and particles from entering. Once the drain is installed, the area is backfilled and the system is left alone unless it clogs.
While an external French drain can operate for ten years or more without the need for maintenance, it's prone to clogging without any warning and can eventually lead to a flooded basement. When there is no filter fiber, sediments can make their way through the stone as years pass and clog the drain, and when the filter fabric is present, that can instead clog with sediments. It may be wise to provide cleanouts, much as is done with sanitary sewers, to provide access for inspection with a camera snake. Also, a French drain that is not installed with a sump pump counts on gravity alone to drain foundation water, and if the house is not located on a hill or near a steep incline, finding this slope can be problematic. Additionally, maintenance on an external French drain involves expensive exterior excavation, which includes removal of walkways, shrubberies, porches, gardens, and anything else along the perimeter.
Installing a French drain around the inside perimeter is most commonly done after the house has been built. Most commonly, this is done in response to a wet basement or right before performing a basement finishing. To install this kind of drain, the perimeter of the basement floor is jackhammered down to the footing and the cement is removed. A layer of stone is laid down, and a perforated drain pipe is laid on top of it. Water is collected from the basement wall floor joint as it enters, and a pump is installed to remove water from the house and away from the foundation.
Once completed, the area, save for a 2 in (5.1 cm) gap around the edge, is cemented over. This gap exists to allow water in from the basement walls. This can be installed very quickly—one to two days by an experienced crew. The system is easy to maintain once installed, and the sump pump will need annual maintenance to perform properly. An interior French drain is much less likely to clog than an exterior, partially due to the fact that it is not sitting underneath several feet of soil.
Interior French drain installation is an effective way to waterproof a basement but requires the use of a sump pump. Many contractors will install plastic sump pumps that can quickly break down or neglect to install a battery backup sump pump, making the basement vulnerable to flooding during power outages. Sump pumps should be installed with a battery backup system in a proper sump liner of 20 US gal (76 L) size or larger to prevent the sump from having too little water and turning on and off continuously.
French drain has evolved significantly from its origins- starting off as a hand-dug ditch, moving on to ceramic tile, PVC pipe, and eventually to the new French drain innovations on the market like WaterGuard and Grate Channel. Each new system is able to address weaknesses of the old as the French drain continues to improve and evolve. For example, whereas Henry French used chippings of tree bark to provide anti-microbial properties, an anti-microbial additive can now be included in the material of the plastic channel.
title: French Drain or Perimeter Drain

Vuge are barefoot fairies singing sad and melancholic songs who will enchant you with their music, take you back to a time that has been long forgotten and make you dance...

Vuge is a band whose music consists of unique and original arrangements of old and forgotten traditional songs from Croatia and other countries.
The band is made up of instruments and vocals that made it unique and original.
The instruments are: violin, flute, cimbalom, double bass, kontra, cajon, darbuka, saxophone. These instruments accompany vocals that are singing in a traditional way typical for each country the songs come from and together with more modern rhythms (jazz, blues, swing) make a unique musical fusion.
Another thing typical for Vuge is the constant interwining of melodies and rhythms of the countries whose songs are performed and an aspiration towards multiculturalism through music.
So, tradition in a modern way, melancholy, archaism, fusion, intertwining and multiculturalism are the main pillars of Vuge.

Vuge su bosonoge vile, tužnog i melankoličnog pjeva, koje će vas svojom čarobnom glazbom odvesti u neka davno zaboravljena vremena i navesti vas na ples...
Vuge su bend koji se bavi obrađivanjem starih, tradicijskih, zaboravljenih pjesama iz Hrvatske, ali i ostalih zemalja na sebi svojstven i originalan način.
Bend sadrži karakterističan instrumentarij i vokale po kojima je postao prepoznatljiv i originalan.
U instrumentariju se nalaze violina, flauta, cimbal, bas, kontra, cajon, tarabuka, saksofon...a on spojen sa arhaičnim vokalima koji njeguju tradicijske načine pjevanja iz zemlje i šire, te modernijim jazz, blues, swing... ritmovima daje unikatan glazbeni spoj.
Uz instrumentarij, karakteristično je i neprekidno ispreplitanje melodija i ritmova svih zemalja čije pjesme izvodimo, te težnja multikulturalizaciji glazbe :)
Dakle tradicija u modernom, melankoličnost, arhaičnost, spajanje, ispreplitanje, multikultura su glavne okosnice koje opisuju Vuge.

description:
Hepatitis-Viren verursachen weltweit die meisten Infektions-Krankheiten.. Die gefährlichste Variante ist Hepatitis C, die Ansteckung erfolgt über infiziertes Blut. Jährlich sterben mehr Menschen an dieser Infektion als an Aids - aber das könnte sich bald ändern. Weil es Hoffnung auf Heilung gibt: Mit neuartigen Therapien, die das Virus selbst angreifen. Ärzte sprechen am Welt-Hepatitis-Tag heute von einem Durchbruch.

Hepatitis C gilt als folgenschwere Krankheit. Das lebensbedrohliche Virus schädigt die Leber. Bisher mussten Hepatitis-C-Patienten das sogenannte Interferon spritzen. Es gab starke Nebenwirkungen. Die Heilungsrate betrug rund 70 Prozent. Die Therapie mit den neuen Medikamenten dagegen verspricht: Es gibt nur sehr geringe Nebenwirkungen. Und eine Heilungsrate von bis zu 95 Prozent.
Therapie "einfacher und effektiver"

Günter Leppert hat seit 30 Jahren Hepatitis-C. Alle Therapien hat er versucht – vergeblich. Er galt als „Non-Responder“. Er bekommt nun an der Uniklinik Mainz das neue Präparat – ein idealer Patient mit großen Chancen auf Heilung, meint Dr. Marcus-Alexander Wörns: "Das, was früher sehr beschwerlich war, insbesondere bei Patienten, die vortherapiert waren, die schon eine weit fortgeschrittene Leberfunktionsstörung haben, all das wird jetzt wesentlich einfacher, effektiver und mit einer kürzeren Behandlungsdauer möglich sein."
Zulassung schon dieses Jahr

Andere befinden sich noch in der Studienphase, sie sollen aber schon bald zugelassen werden. Und, so Wörns:“ Patienten die jetzt schon einer Therapie bedürfen, denen können wir jetzt schon hoch effektiv helfen."

Von den neuen Medikamenten, die jetzt auf den Markt kamen, ist Sofosbuvir gerade zugelassen und auf Rezept erhältlich. Andere befinden sich noch in der Studienphase, sie sollen aber schon bald zugelassen werden. Und, so Wörns:“ Patienten die jetzt schon einer Therapie bedürfen, denen können wir jetzt schon hoch effektiv helfen." Eine Therapie kostet insgesamt etwa 100.000 Euro. Die Krankenkassen übernehmen die Kosten.

C'est ma bouche , qui taff et qui t'éclaircit quand t'es louche. 
Elle accouche, et tu veux pas l'avouer mais je sens qu'elle touche. 
Elle tache tous tes clichés proprement idiots. 
C'est pas un hasard si elle te fait penser à John Doe.  
Elle a bossé pour toi, elle donne ce qui est important.  
Si elle t'aime bien, elle te souri en partant. 
Elle expire de la fumée d'expert. 
Elle carbure, elle aspire mais ne crois pas qu'elle s'perd. 
Elle fait l'sport des qu'elle court et qu'elle décrit le coeur d'un couplet qui creusera l'écart 
avec eux, les porcs qui perdent la boule et qui oublient qu'ils avaient des queues.
Encore pas plus tard qu'hier elle a fait taire des bruyants.
Il a suffit d'faire vriller des vers brillants.
Ma bouche elle a 32 dents, elle mâche tout ce qui rentre dedans
et elle crache les morceaux sur les grands d'devant.
Mais la langue y tourne 7 fois avant d'y vanter l'talent.
Elle a tellement vu les gencives gouter la vie et son talon.
Ca faisait gonfler ma bouche, les tissu injectés d'sang.
Et celui qui protège les dents il était absent 
mais elle est toujours là; malgré les femmes qui l'ont conquise,
l'ont croquée, avant d'finir sur de longues bises.
Alors elle vise tes tympans, si t'es plein d'vice ou qu't'es une timpu.
Si ton canapé ne lui plait plus, elle comble le blanc quand il en reste un peu.
Ma dentition voit passer le fruit de mon ambition :
Du bruit et du grand frisson qui part en mission.
Elle vise le monde, je veux qu'elle inonde bien plus que visuellement.
Mépriser les gens c'est devenu la mode mais elle passe et t'embrasse la main.
Ma bouche, elle est à l'aise pour articuler.
Elle fait rouler des chuchotements quand les autres sont parti gueuler.
Elle est centré, sans trop d'folie ni d'parole.
Elle en a qu'une, mais elle est est colorée comme Warhole.
Elle a son rôle à coeur depuis l'époque de l'école,
depuis qu'entre potes on décolle parce que le sol nous désole.
Il est plein de drôles d'acteurs, avec le froque sur l'épaule.
On veut que la foule se dévoile avant de plier les gaules.
On veut que tu sois notre égal et que tu y penses quand tu t'couches.
Allez j'ferme ma bouche, j'crois que je me suis assez régalé.
title: Le Bon Nob # 32 - Ma bouche

description:
LOS ANGELES (KABC) -- Unnecessary and excessive: That's what one man is calling a fierce encounter he captured on video between a CHP officer and a woman two days ago.

The video starts rolling right around 6:30 p.m. Tuesday. A woman walking on the eastbound 10 Freeway near the La Brea onramp is tackled on the roadside shoulder by a CHP officer. The officer unleashes a barrage of punches to her face.

David Diaz shot the video of the violent confrontation from his car. Diaz says he has no idea what spurred the beating, just that before he got his camera out he saw the officer chasing the woman around a pickup truck on the onramp.

The truck pulled away and Diaz started recording. Eventually another man runs over to assist the officer. Diaz assumed it was an undercover officer.

The CHP wouldn't talk with Eyewitness News on camera about this incident, but in a written statement, CHP said the officer ordered the woman to stop, but she ignored him. Fearing she would be hurt, the CHP says the officer tried placing her under arrest.

"A physical altercation ensued as the pedestrian continued to resist arrest, at which point a plain clothes, off duty officer assisted in applying the handcuffs," the CHP said in the statement.

But Diaz says he's still disturbed by the violent response of the officer... that the woman didn't seem to be fighting back and could have been subdued in a much safer manner.

"There was no weapons, it's obviously excess force at this point," said Diaz. "He could have easily calmed her down. You can use strength without punching."

The CHP said the woman refused to give her name. She was booked as "Jane Doe" and taken to a local hospital for mental and physical evaluation.
